[{"location":"convergence/#Convergence-Utilities","page":"Convergence","title":"Convergence Utilities","text":"PenguinAnalysis.jl includes helpers for empirical order studies from error sequences.","category":"section"},{"location":"convergence/#Pairwise-Orders","page":"Convergence","title":"Pairwise Orders","text":"For matching vectors errors and mesh scales hs, the pairwise slopes are:\n\nord = pairwise_orders(errors, hs)\n\nFor dyadic refinement (h_{k+1} = h_k / 2), use:\n\nord2 = pairwise_orders(errors)","category":"section"},{"location":"convergence/#Overall-Order","page":"Convergence","title":"Overall Order","text":"Global log-log slope from least squares:\n\np = overall_order(errors, hs)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#API","page":"API","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#PenguinAnalysis.CellMeasure","page":"API","title":"PenguinAnalysis.CellMeasure","text":"CellMeasure(V; celltype=nothing)\nCellMeasure(; V, celltype=nothing)\nCellMeasure(obj)\n\nLightweight holder for wet measure V and optional celltype tags.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#PenguinAnalysis.region_mask","page":"API","title":"PenguinAnalysis.region_mask","text":"region_mask(cm::CellMeasure, region::Symbol)\n\nReturn a boolean mask selecting active cells in region (:all, :cut, :full).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#PenguinAnalysis.lp_error","page":"API","title":"PenguinAnalysis.lp_error","text":"lp_error(u, u_exact, geom; p=2, region=:all, relative=false)\n\nCompute the weighted discrete global L^p error for one field or an aggregated field tree.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#PenguinAnalysis.lp_errors","page":"API","title":"PenguinAnalysis.lp_errors","text":"lp_errors(u, u_exact, geom; p=2, region=:all, relative=false)\n\nCompute weighted discrete L^p errors leaf-by-leaf, preserving tuple tree structure.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#PenguinAnalysis.lp_error_report","page":"API","title":"PenguinAnalysis.lp_error_report","text":"lp_error_report(u, u_exact, geom; p=2, region=:all, relative=false)\n\nCompute weighted discrete error and return an ErrorReport with diagnostics.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#PenguinAnalysis.ErrorReport","page":"API","title":"PenguinAnalysis.ErrorReport","text":"ErrorReport\n\nSummary container returned by lp_error_report.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#PenguinAnalysis.pairwise_orders","page":"API","title":"PenguinAnalysis.pairwise_orders","text":"pairwise_orders(errors, hs)\npairwise_orders(errors)\n\nCompute pairwise convergence orders from error sequences, with optional mesh sizes hs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#PenguinAnalysis.overall_order","page":"API","title":"PenguinAnalysis.overall_order","text":"overall_order(errors, hs)\n\nReturn the global log-log slope from a least-squares fit of errors against hs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"examples/#Examples","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#Scalar-Field","page":"Examples","title":"Scalar Field","text":"using PenguinAnalysis\n\nV = [0.2, 0.7, 1.0]\nct = [-1, -1, 1]\ngeom = CellMeasure(V; celltype=ct)\n\nu  = [1.0, 0.8, 0.1]\nue = [1.1, 0.7, 0.0]\n\nl2_all = lp_error(u, ue, geom; p=2, region=:all)\nl2_cut = lp_error(u, ue, geom; p=2, region=:cut)","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#Nested-Tuple-Trees","page":"Examples","title":"Nested Tuple Trees","text":"using PenguinAnalysis\n\nu = (ux, uy)\nue = (uxe, uye)\ng = (gx, gy)\n\nerr = lp_error(u, ue, g; p=2, region=:all)\nerrs = lp_errors(u, ue, g; p=2, region=:all)","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#Relative-Error","page":"Examples","title":"Relative Error","text":"rep = lp_error_report(u, ue, g; p=2, relative=true)\nratio = rep.value","category":"section"},{"location":"#PenguinAnalysis.jl","page":"Home","title":"PenguinAnalysis.jl","text":"Welcome to the PenguinAnalysis documentation. This package provides solver-agnostic weighted discrete error norms and convergence utilities for array fields and nested field trees.\n\nPages\n\nAPI\nExamples\nConvergence Utilities\n\nRegion semantics\n\n:all: active cells with V > 0\n:cut: active cut cells (celltype == -1)\n:full: active full cells (celltype == 1)\n\ncelltype is required for :cut and :full. CellMeasure(obj) accepts both celltype and cell_type conventions.","category":"section"}]
